glosses.gloss: A hypothetical organic phenomenon by which living organisms are created from nonliving matter
Spontaneous generation refers to an obsolete body of thought on the ordinary formation of living organisms without descent from similar organisms.
Abiogenesis, or informally the origin of life, is the natural process by which life arises from non-living matter, such as simple organic compounds.
